OL,3,CMother speaks of relief as son's
OL,4,Cmedication becomes available on NHS
OL,6,F"I didn't hear anything and I thought
OL,7,Fno news must be good news," she
OL,8,Fcontinued.
OL,10,F"The week before Christmas he had
OL,11,Fanother seizure, so I took him to A
OL,12,Fand E, whilst the MRI was flagged as
OL,13,Fhaving a brain tumour present, they
OL,14,Fhad kind of lost it in the system."
OL,16,FIt was when Alexander returned to the
OL,17,Femergency department following another
OL,18,Fseizure in December 2020, the scan
OL,19,Fimages were recovered and the family
OL,20,Fwere informed he had a brain tumour -
OL,21,Ftwo months after the scan.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/19
