OL,3,CMother speaks of relief as son's
OL,4,Cmedication becomes available on NHS
OL,6,F"The way we found out, in A and E, and
OL,7,FXander was with me - I imagine usually
OL,8,Fthey have all these ways they tell
OL,9,Fchildren you've got a brain tumour,
OL,10,Fbut unfortunately we were told there
OL,11,Fand then," she said.
OL,13,F"Xander is a really bright boy, he was
OL,14,Freally interested in the human body
OL,15,Fand knows how important the brain is
OL,16,Fso it was really hard for him to find
OL,17,Fout that way."
OL,19,FMedics believed the tumour was slow
OL,20,Fgrowing, but Ms Josephs urged them to
OL,21,Fperform surgery in January 2021.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/19
